This paper discusses the use of ontologies and knowledge representation in solving database problems, specifically through the use of Inductive Logic Programming (ILP). This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, but the most relevant is likely cs.DB (Databases), as the paper focuses on database problems. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these fields also deal with knowledge representation and reasoning.
